==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Trichromatic
<hw>Tri`chro*mat"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>tri-</ets> + <ets>chromatic</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Having or existing in three different phases of color; having three
distinct color varieties; -- said of certain birds and
insects.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trichromatism</ent>⟦br⟧
